wanting a baby well i am engaged and i have always wanted kids ever since i was really young and no i was never a stupid girl i never tried i am now and i cant stop thinking about having kids and having a family everytime i see mothers with there kids it makes me sad but i no that this is not a good time and there is no way that i could have kids right now does anyone no ways to distract myself from this kind of thinking i've seen babies be born i've raised younger brothers aand sisters and have helped my best friend raise her baby that she had at years old but for some reason i still want one none of these things change my mind what can i do help please i can understand how you feel although i am a bit older than you i cant help the longing in my heart when i see a little baby my husband and i have been trying for years but i will tell you that i am glad we have had this time to get used to each other and fall into a routine i think it is important that you try to give you and your fiance time to enjoy being married to each other because once you have a child your relationship will change allover again maybe you should get a puppy or kitten i know it is not a real substitute but it will give you a loving little one to lavish with all that motherly love you have on another note how does your fiance feel about having a child does he want to have one right away or does he want to wait talk with him because once you guys are married it is his decision too maybe he will surprise you and will want to start a family with you right away good luck and god bless i will be praying for you and your new family Charmed EastEnders Pitaten Kodocha Friends Humphrey Bogart Jon Secada Married... with Children The Catcher in the Rye Baby Blues Infantilism Care Bears Rugrats Good Times Hollyoaks One Tree Hill (TV series) One Life to Live Atomic Kitten The Fairly OddParents Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Springfield Elementary School Ranma __